description.narrative: The Program objective of the Water Resources Development and Sustainable Ecosystems Management APL is to enhance regional coordination, development, and management of the Niger Basin's water resources. The development objective of the Kandadji Project is to increase the capacity for energy generation and enhance the availability and management of water for agriculture development in the Niger part of the Niger Basin, and to improve livelihoods in the Tillaberi region.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Biodiversity Offset Area | Description :Niger shall have caused the Biodiversity Offset Area (A) to have beenlegally established and (B) to be operating in accordance with the provisions of the Wild Life and Natural Habitat Management Plan,all in a manner consistent with OP/BP 4.12; and Niger shall maintain the BOA ensure that sufficient resources are allocated to theoperation. | Due Date :15-Sep-2017

Finance Agreement :HCDNV Restructuring | Description :The HCDNV has been restructured in a manner acceptable to the Associationpursuant to a legal instrument in form and substance satisfactory to the Association. | Due Date :13-Mar-2013

Finance Agreement :IDA Credit Agreement | Description :The IDA Credit Agreement has been executed and delivered and all conditionsprecedent to its effectiveness or to the right of the Republic of Niger to make withdrawals under it (other than the effectivenessof this Agreement) has been fulfilled. | Due Date :13-Mar-2013

Finance Agreement :IDA Grant Agreement | Description :The IDA Grant Agreement has been executed and delivered and all conditionsprecedent to its effectiveness or to the right of NBA to make withdrawals under it (other than the effectiveness of this Agreement)has been fulfilled. | Due Date :13-Mar-2013

Finance Agreement :Level of Impoundment | Description :Niger shall have confirmed the level of impoundment of the reservoir for theoperation of the Kandadji dam and completed the censusof Displaced Persons to be included in the Resettlement Action Plan 2 in amanner acceptable to the Association (also a condition ofthe first IDA disbursement for the financing of the power plant). | DueDate :31-Dec-2014

Finance Agreement :Memorandum of Understanding between HCDNV and Niger Ministry | Description :HCDNV shall enter into andthereafter maintain throughout the implementation of Part 3 of the Project, a memorandum of understanding with Niger’s Ministryresponsible for agriculture, for the implementation of irrigation and local development activities. | Due Date :07-Jan-2013

Finance Agreement :Project Implementation Manual | Description :The Project Implementation Manual has been revised and adopted bythe Recipient for the Project in form and substance satisfactory to the Association. | Due Date :13-Mar-2013

Finance Agreement :Project Implementation Manual | Description: No later than six months after effectiveness, the ProjectImplementation Manual has been revised and adopted by the Recipient for the Project in form and substance satisfactory to theAssociation. Due date: 15-Jun-2021

Finance Agreement: Dam Operation and Maintenance Plan | Description: No later than 6 months prior to the projected date ofimpoundment of the reservoir of the Kandadji dam, Niger shall adopt the Dam Operation and Maintenance Plan, in form and substanceacceptable to the Association and the Dam Safety Panel. | Due Date:15-Jun-2026

Finance Agreement: Dam and Plant Operational Arrangements | Description: No later than the date falling one year before theexpected date of impoundment of the reservoir of the Kandadji dam, Niger shall establish an arrangement satisfactory to theAssociation for the operation of the dam and the plant included in Part 2 of the Project. | Due Date : 15-Dec-2025

Finance Agreement: Emergency Preparedness Plan | Description: No later than the date falling 1 year prior to the projected date ofimpoundment of the reservoir of the Kandadji dam, Niger shall have furnished the final draft of the Emergency Preparedness Plan tothe Association and the Dam Safety Panel for review. | Due Date: 15-Dec-2025

Finance Agreement: Power Purchase Agreement | Description: No later than the date falling nine (9) months before the expected dateof impoundment of the reservoir of the Kandadji dam, Niger shall have caused a power purchase agreement in form and substancesatisfactory to the Association to be entered into between the operator and NIGELEC. | Due Date :15-Mar-2026

Finance Agreement: Resettlement sites and related irrigation perimeters are 100% completed and functional prior to arrival ofDisplaced Persons | Description: No later than the date 12 months prior to the projected date of the Kandadji dam reservoirimpoundment, Niger shall have completed the resettlement sites and related irrigation perimeters identified in RAP 2A in a mannersatisfactory to the Association and in accordance with the provisions of RAP 2A |Due Date: 15-Dec-2025.

Finance Agreement:Resettlement of 100% of Displaced Persons | Description:No later than the date 6 months prior to the projecteddate of the Kandadji dam reservoir impoundment, Niger shall have completed the resettlement of 100% of the Displaced Personsidentified in the RAP2A in a manner satisfactory to the Association and in accordance with with the provisions of the RAP2A. |DueDate:15-Jun-2026
